# Requirements Documentation
## Bytes Battle - Agricultural Export Platform

**Version:** 1.0.0  
**Last Updated:** February 12, 2026  
**Project Type:** Web Application (Prototype)

## 1. System Requirements

### 1.1 Client-Side Requirements

#### Minimum Hardware Requirements:
- **Processor:** 1.6 GHz or faster
- **RAM:** 2 GB minimum, 4 GB recommended
- **Storage:** 100 MB free disk space
- **Display:** 1024x768 resolution minimum
- **Network:** Broadband internet connection (1 Mbps+)

#### Supported Operating Systems:
- âœ… Windows 10/11
- âœ… macOS 10.13 (High Sierra) or later
- âœ… Linux (Ubuntu 18.04+, Fedora 30+, etc.)
- âœ… iOS 12+ (Safari)
- âœ… Android 8.0+ (Chrome)

#### Supported Web Browsers:
| Browser | Minimum Version | Recommended |
|---------|----------------|-------------|
| Google Chrome | 60+ | Latest |
| Mozilla Firefox | 55+ | Latest |
| Safari | 11+ | Latest |
| Microsoft Edge | 79+ (Chromium) | Latest |
| Opera | 47+ | Latest |
| Brave | 1.0+ | Latest |

#### Required Browser Features:
- CSS3 support (Grid, Flexbox, Gradients, Transforms)
- HTML5 support
- JavaScript ES6+ support
- Smooth scroll API
- Form validation API
- LocalStorage (for future enhancements)
- Fetch API (for future backend integration)

### 1.2 Server-Side Requirements (Future Implementation)

#### For Development Server:
- **Python:** 3.7+ (for simple HTTP server)
- **Node.js:** 14+ (optional, for http-server)
- **PHP:** 7.4+ (optional)

#### For Production Deployment:
- **Web Server:** Apache 2.4+, Nginx 1.18+, or any static file server
- **SSL/TLS:** Certificate required for HTTPS
- **CDN:** Optional but recommended for global distribution

---

## 2. Functional Requirements

### 2.1 User Interface Requirements

#### FR-UI-001: Navigation System
**Priority:** HIGH  
**Description:** The platform must provide a sticky navigation header with smooth scrolling to all major sections.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Navigation header remains visible on scroll
- All navigation links must work
- Smooth scroll animation (500ms duration)
- Active section highlighting
- Mobile-responsive hamburger menu (if implemented)

#### FR-UI-002: Hero Section
**Priority:** HIGH  
**Description:** Landing page must display compelling hero section with call-to-action.

#### FR-UI-003: Vegetables Catalog
**Priority:** HIGH  
**Description:** Display comprehensive catalog of exportable vegetables.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Minimum 12 vegetable entries
- Each card must include:
  - Vegetable name and icon
  - Price per kg (USD and INR)
  - Origin states
  - Growing season
  - Varieties
  - Description (50-100 words)
- Responsive grid layout (1-3 columns based on screen size)
- Hover effects on cards
- Price clarity disclaimer

#### FR-UI-004: Farming Regions
**Priority:** MEDIUM  
**Description:** Showcase major agricultural regions of India.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Minimum 10 regional cards
- Each card includes:
  - Region name
  - Key crops
  - Climate information
  - Soil types
  - Specialty/unique features
- Responsive grid layout
- Hover effects

#### FR-UI-005: Economic Impact Section
**Priority:** MEDIUM  
**Description:** Display economic benefits and statistics.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- 12 impact cards with icons
- Statistics section with 3-4 key metrics
- 5-year projection display
- "Why This Model Works" explanation
- Responsive layout

#### FR-UI-006: Contact Form
**Priority:** HIGH  
**Description:** Functional contact/inquiry form for stakeholders.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Required fields: Name, Email, Phone, Type, Message
- Optional fields: Region, Vegetables of Interest
- Dropdown for stakeholder type (Farmer, Buyer, Distributor, Investor, Other)
- Real-time validation
- Success message display
- Form reset after submission
- Auto-hide success message (5 seconds)

#### FR-UI-007: Footer
**Priority:** LOW  
**Description:** Informational footer with links and legal information.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Company name and tagline
- Quick links to all sections
- Copyright notice
- Disclaimer about prototype nature
- Regional office information

### 2.2 Interaction Requirements

#### FR-INT-001: Form Submission
**Priority:** HIGH  
**Description:** Handle contact form submissions with validation.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Client-side validation before submission
- Prevent submission if required fields empty
- Email format validation
- Phone number format validation
- Success/error message display
- Smooth scroll to confirmation

#### FR-INT-002: Smooth Scrolling
**Priority:** MEDIUM  
**Description:** All anchor links must use smooth scroll behavior.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Navigation links scroll smoothly
- CTA button scrolls to contact form
- 500ms animation duration
- Works on all supported browsers

#### FR-INT-003: Responsive Behavior
**Priority:** HIGH  
**Description:** Layout adapts to different screen sizes.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Desktop: 3-column grid for cards
- Tablet: 2-column grid
- Mobile: 1-column grid
- Text remains readable on all devices
- Images scale appropriately
- No horizontal scrolling on mobile

---

## 3. Non-Functional Requirements

### 3.1 Usability Requirements

#### NFR-USE-001: Accessibility
**Priority:** HIGH  
**Requirement:** Platform must be accessible to users with disabilities.

**Standards:**
- WCAG 2.1 Level AA compliance
- Semantic HTML structure
- Proper heading hierarchy (H1 â†’ H2 â†’ H3)
- Alt text for images (when implemented)
- Keyboard navigation support
- Minimum color contrast ratio: 4.5:1 for text
- Focus indicators on interactive elements

#### NFR-USE-002: User Experience
**Priority:** HIGH  
**Requirement:** Platform must provide intuitive, pleasant user experience.

**Metrics:**
- First-time users can navigate without instructions
- Average time to find vegetable information: <30 seconds
- Average time to complete contact form: <2 minutes
- User satisfaction score: >4.0/5.0

#### NFR-USE-003: Mobile Experience
**Priority:** HIGH  
**Requirement:** Mobile-first responsive design.

**Criteria:**
- Touch-friendly tap targets (minimum 44x44px)
- No pinch-zoom required
- Fast load times on 3G/4G networks
- Readable text without zooming (minimum 16px body text)

### 3.2 Performance Requirements

#### NFR-PERF-001: Page Load Speed
**Priority:** HIGH  
**Requirement:** Fast initial page load and rendering.

**Metrics:**
- First Contentful Paint (FCP): <1.8 seconds
- Largest Contentful Paint (LCP): <2.5 seconds
- Time to Interactive (TTI): <3.8 seconds
- Total page weight: <500 KB (without images)
- First Meaningful Paint: <1.5 seconds

#### NFR-PERF-002: Runtime Performance
**Priority:** MEDIUM  
**Requirement:** Smooth interactions and animations.

**Criteria:**
- Embedded CSS (no external stylesheet requests)
- Embedded JavaScript (no external script requests)
- Minimal inline SVG usage
- No render-blocking resources
- Browser caching enabled (when deployed)

### 3.3 Reliability Requirements

#### NFR-REL-001: Browser Compatibility
**Priority:** HIGH  
**Requirement:** Consistent functionality across browsers.

**Coverage:**
- 100% feature parity on Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge
- Graceful degradation on older browsers
- No breaking errors on any supported browser

#### NFR-REL-002: Error Handling
**Priority:** MEDIUM  
**Requirement:** Graceful error handling.

**Criteria:**
- Form validation errors displayed clearly
- No JavaScript console errors
- Fallback content for missing images
- User-friendly error messages

### 3.4 Maintainability Requirements

#### NFR-MAIN-001: Code Quality
**Priority:** MEDIUM  
**Requirement:** Clean, maintainable code structure.

**Standards:**
- Consistent indentation (4 spaces)
- Clear variable and function naming
- Comments for complex logic
- Separation of concerns (HTML/CSS/JS)
- Semantic HTML elements

#### NFR-MAIN-002: Documentation
**Priority:** MEDIUM  
**Requirement:** Comprehensive documentation.

## 4. Technical Requirements

### 4.1 Frontend Technologies

#### TR-FE-001: HTML5
**Requirement:** Valid, semantic HTML5 markup.

**Specifications:**
- DOCTYPE: `<!DOCTYPE html>`
- Character encoding: UTF-8
- Viewport meta tag for responsive design
- Semantic elements: `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<section>`, `<footer>`
- Valid HTML according to W3C validator

#### TR-FE-002: CSS3
**Requirement:** Modern CSS3 for styling and layout.

**Features Required:**
- CSS Grid for layout
- Flexbox for component alignment
- CSS Gradients for visual effects
- CSS Transforms for hover effects
- CSS Transitions for smooth animations
- Media queries for responsive design
- Custom properties (CSS variables) - optional

#### TR-FE-003: JavaScript (ES6+)
**Requirement:** Vanilla JavaScript for interactivity.

**Features Required:**
- Arrow functions
- Template literals
- `const` and `let` declarations
- DOM manipulation methods
- Event listeners
- Form validation
- Smooth scroll API

### 4.2 Architecture Requirements

#### TR-ARCH-001: Single File Architecture
**Requirement:** Complete website in single HTML file.

**Rationale:**
- Easy deployment
- No build process required
- Fast initial load (single HTTP request)
- Portable and self-contained

#### TR-ARCH-002: Progressive Enhancement
**Requirement:** Core functionality without JavaScript.

**Criteria:**
- All content visible without JavaScript
- Form submits (even if not processed)
- Navigation links work
- JavaScript enhances experience only

### 4.3 Data Requirements

#### TR-DATA-001: Static Data
**Requirement:** All data embedded in HTML.

**Data Entities:**
- Vegetables (12+ entries)
- Farming Regions (10+ entries)
- Economic Impact Statistics
- Contact Information
- Regional Offices

#### TR-DATA-002: Data Structure
**Requirement:** Structured data in HTML cards.

**Example Structure:**
```html
<div class="veg-card">
    <div class="veg-header">
        <h3>ðŸ¥” Vegetable Name</h3>
        <div class="veg-price">$X.XX/kg</div>
    </div>
    <div class="veg-body">
        <div class="veg-info"><strong>Field:</strong> Value</div>
    </div>
</div>
```

