## 5. User Requirements

### 5.1 User Personas

#### Persona 1: Indian Farmer
**Needs:**
- Find export opportunities
- Understand pricing
- Contact buyers directly
- Learn about successful regions

**Requirements:**
- Simple, clear information
- Regional language support (future)
- Mobile-friendly interface
- Easy contact form

#### Persona 2: International Buyer
**Needs:**
- Browse available vegetables
- Check pricing and availability
- Understand sourcing regions
- Contact suppliers

**Requirements:**
- Detailed product information
- Professional presentation
- Clear pricing
- Easy inquiry process

#### Persona 3: Distributor/Agent
**Needs:**
- Partner opportunities
- Market information
- Contact channels
- Economic impact data

**Requirements:**
- Business-focused content
- Statistics and metrics
- Professional contact form
- Regional office information

#### Persona 4: Investor
**Needs:**
- Economic impact data
- Growth projections
- Market size information
- Contact for investment inquiries

**Requirements:**
- Data-driven content
- Future projections
- Professional presentation
- Business contact options

### 5.2 User Journey Requirements

#### UJ-001: First-Time Visitor
**Journey:**
1. Land on hero section
2. Scroll through vegetables catalog
3. Explore farming regions
4. Review economic impact
5. Fill contact form

**Requirements:**
- Clear value proposition in hero
- Engaging visual design
- Easy navigation
- Compelling call-to-action

#### UJ-002: Returning User
**Journey:**
1. Quick navigation to specific section
2. Review updated information
3. Contact form submission

**Requirements:**
- Sticky navigation for quick access
- Smooth scrolling
- Form pre-fill (future enhancement)

---

## 6. Data Requirements

### 6.1 Content Requirements

#### DR-CONT-001: Vegetables Data
**Required Fields:**
- Name (String, required)
- Icon/Emoji (Unicode character)
- Price USD (Decimal, required)
- Price INR (Decimal, required)
- Origin States (Array/String, required)
- Season (String, required)
- Varieties (String, required)
- Description (String, 50-150 words, required)

**Validation:**
- Prices must be positive numbers
- Prices must be in correct currency
- Description must be informative

#### DR-CONT-002: Regions Data
**Required Fields:**
- Region Name (String, required)
- Icon/Emoji (Unicode character)
- Key Crops (String, required)
- Climate (String, required)
- Specialty (String, required)
- Soil Type (String, optional)
- Notable Features (String, optional)

#### DR-CONT-003: Statistics Data
**Required Fields:**
- Metric Name (String, required)
- Value (Number or String, required)
- Unit/Label (String, required)

**Examples:**
- "500+ Partner Farmers"
- "25+ Countries Served"
- "10,000+ Tons Exported Annually"

### 6.2 Form Data Requirements

#### DR-FORM-001: Contact Form Data
**Required Fields:**
- Full Name (String, max 100 chars)
- Email (Email format, max 100 chars)
- Phone (String, max 20 chars)
- Type (Enum: Farmer, Buyer, Distributor, Investor, Other)
- Message (Text, max 1000 chars)

**Optional Fields:**
- Region (String, max 100 chars)
- Vegetables of Interest (String, max 200 chars)

**Validation Rules:**
- Email must match pattern: `^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$`
- Phone must contain only digits, spaces, +, -, ()
- All required fields must be non-empty
- Message minimum length: 10 characters

---

## 7. Security Requirements

### 7.1 Current Implementation (Prototype)

#### SR-CURR-001: Client-Side Validation
**Requirement:** Basic form validation.

**Implementation:**
- HTML5 required attributes
- Email type validation
- JavaScript validation before submission

#### SR-CURR-002: No Sensitive Data Storage
**Requirement:** No user data stored locally.

**Implementation:**
- Form data logged to console only (for demo)
- No cookies
- No localStorage usage
- No backend submission

### 7.2 Future Implementation Requirements

#### SR-FUT-001: HTTPS Only
**Priority:** CRITICAL  
**Requirement:** All traffic must use HTTPS.

**Rationale:**
- Protect user data in transit
- SEO benefits
- Browser trust indicators

#### SR-FUT-002: Input Sanitization
**Priority:** HIGH  
**Requirement:** Sanitize all user inputs server-side.

**Protection Against:**
- XSS (Cross-Site Scripting)
- SQL Injection
- CSRF (Cross-Site Request Forgery)
- Code Injection

#### SR-FUT-003: Rate Limiting
**Priority:** MEDIUM  
**Requirement:** Limit form submissions to prevent spam.

**Specifications:**
- Max 5 submissions per IP per hour
- CAPTCHA for suspicious activity
- Honeypot fields for bot detection

#### SR-FUT-004: Data Privacy
**Priority:** HIGH  
**Requirement:** Comply with data protection regulations.

**Standards:**
- GDPR compliance (for EU users)
- Clear privacy policy
- User consent for data collection
- Right to data deletion

---

## 8. Performance Requirements

### 8.1 Load Time Requirements

#### PR-LOAD-001: Initial Load
**Metric:** Time to First Byte (TTFB)  
**Target:** <200ms  
**Measurement:** From request to first byte received

#### PR-LOAD-002: First Contentful Paint
**Metric:** FCP  
**Target:** <1.8 seconds  
**Measurement:** Time until first text/image rendered

#### PR-LOAD-003: Largest Contentful Paint
**Metric:** LCP  
**Target:** <2.5 seconds  
**Measurement:** Time until largest element rendered

#### PR-LOAD-004: Time to Interactive
**Metric:** TTI  
**Target:** <3.8 seconds  
**Measurement:** Time until page fully interactive

### 8.2 Runtime Performance Requirements

#### PR-RUN-001: Scroll Performance
**Metric:** Frames Per Second (FPS)  
**Target:** 60 FPS  
**Measurement:** Scroll smoothness

#### PR-RUN-002: Animation Performance
**Metric:** FPS during animations  
**Target:** 60 FPS  
**Measurement:** Hover effects, transitions

#### PR-RUN-003: Form Responsiveness
**Metric:** Input lag  
**Target:** <100ms  
**Measurement:** Time from keystroke to display

### 8.3 Resource Usage Requirements

#### PR-RES-001: Page Weight
**Metric:** Total transfer size  
**Target:** <500 KB (HTML + CSS + JS)  
**Measurement:** Network transfer size

#### PR-RES-002: Memory Usage
**Metric:** JavaScript heap size  
**Target:** <50 MB  
**Measurement:** Browser memory consumption

#### PR-RES-003: CPU Usage
**Metric:** Processing time  
**Target:** <500ms for script execution  
**Measurement:** Total JavaScript execution time

---

## 9. Compliance Requirements

### 9.1 Web Standards Compliance

#### CR-WEB-001: HTML Validation
**Standard:** W3C HTML5 Validator  
**Requirement:** Zero errors, minimal warnings  
**Validation URL:** https://validator.w3.org/

#### CR-WEB-002: CSS Validation
**Standard:** W3C CSS Validator  
**Requirement:** Valid CSS3  
**Validation URL:** https://jigsaw.w3.org/css-validator/

#### CR-WEB-003: Accessibility Compliance
**Standard:** WCAG 2.1 Level AA  
**Requirement:** Pass automated accessibility tests

**Testing Tools:**
- WAVE (Web Accessibility Evaluation Tool)
- axe DevTools
- Lighthouse Accessibility Audit

### 9.2 Legal Compliance Requirements

#### CR-LEG-001: Disclaimer
**Requirement:** Clear prototype disclaimer.

**Content:**
- "This is a PROTOTYPE/EDUCATIONAL PROJECT"
- "All email addresses are fictional"
- "Phone numbers are not functional"
- "Prices are illustrative only"
- "Not affiliated with APEDA or government organizations"

#### CR-LEG-002: Copyright Notice
**Requirement:** Copyright and attribution.

**Content:**
- Copyright year and owner
- Open source license (MIT)
- Attribution for data sources

#### CR-LEG-003: Data Usage Notice
**Requirement:** Privacy and data handling statement.

**Content:**
- "Contact form does not actually submit data"
- "For educational/portfolio use only"
- Future: Privacy policy link

